    <fr:title text="Cone over a simplicial set">Cone over a simplicial set</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
    <fr:date>
      <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
      <fr:month>3</fr:month>
      <fr:day>9</fr:day>
    </fr:date>
    <fr:authors>
      <fr:author>
        <fr:link type="local" href="trebor.xml" addr="trebor" title="Trebor">Trebor</fr:link>
      </fr:author>
    </fr:authors>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Given a simplicial set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:strong>cone</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X^\triangleleft ]]></fr:tex> is defined by the <fr:link type="local" href="htt-000B.xml" addr="htt-000B" title="Join of (augmented) simplicial set">join</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1 \star  X]]></fr:tex> with the singleton. Dually, the <fr:strong>cocone</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X^\triangleright ]]></fr:tex> is defined by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \star  1]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
      <fr:frontmatter>
