        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>601</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">htt-000E</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>htt-000E.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Slice of simplicial sets">Slice of simplicial sets</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>3</fr:month>
              <fr:day>9</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link type="local" href="trebor.xml" addr="trebor" title="Trebor">Trebor</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Given a simplicial set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> and a vertex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p : 1 \to  Y]]></fr:tex>, we define the <fr:strong>slice</fr:strong> simplicial set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_{/p}]]></fr:tex> by the universal property that maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \to  Y_{/p}]]></fr:tex> are in natural bijection with maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K^{\triangleright } \to  Y]]></fr:tex> from the <fr:link type="local" href="htt-000C.xml" addr="htt-000C" title="Cone over a simplicial set">cocone</fr:link> such that the cocone point is mapped to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>More generally, given simplicial sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X, Y]]></fr:tex> and a map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:strong>slice</fr:strong> simplicial set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_{/p}]]></fr:tex> is defined by the universal property that maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \to  Y_{/p}]]></fr:tex> is in bijection with maps <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K \star  X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> such that the restriction <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \hookrightarrow  K \star  X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Dually, we can define <fr:strong>coslice</fr:strong> simplicial sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_{p/}]]></fr:tex> using cones <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K^{\triangleleft } \to  Y]]></fr:tex>. When <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link type="local" href="htt-0001.xml" addr="htt-0001" title="-Category"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\infty ]]></fr:tex>-category</fr:link>, we also call them <fr:em>overcategories</fr:em> and <fr:em>undercategories</fr:em>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
