            <fr:title text="Join of (augmented) simplicial set">Join of (augmented) simplicial set</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>3</fr:month>
              <fr:day>9</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link type="local" href="trebor.xml" addr="trebor" title="Trebor">Trebor</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Given two <fr:link type="local" href="htt-000A.xml" addr="htt-000A" title="Augmented simplicial set">augmented simplicial sets</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X, Y]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:strong>join</fr:strong> is given by a Day convolution. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\oplus ]]></fr:tex> denote the ordinal sum. Then we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[m] \oplus  [n] = [m+n+1]]]></fr:tex>, since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[m]]]></fr:tex> represents the linear order with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(m+1)]]></fr:tex> elements. We have
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[(X \star  Y)_k = \int ^{m, n} X_m \times  Y_n \times  \hom ([k], [m] \oplus  [n]).]]></fr:tex>
  More concretely, the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex>-simplices of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \star  Y]]></fr:tex> is given by the disjoint union of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X_m \times  Y_n]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k = m + n + 1]]></fr:tex>. The face and degeneracy maps act on the corresponding components. Note that this is non-symmetric since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> handles the first few face maps, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> handles the last ones.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Given two simplicial sets, the join of their <fr:link type="local" href="htt-000A.xml" addr="htt-000A" title="Augmented simplicial set">codiscrete augmentation</fr:link> is again a codiscrete augmented simplicial set. We define the simplicial join <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \star  Y \in  \mathsf {sSet}]]></fr:tex> by forgetting its augmentation.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
